                    font-style: normal;
                    font-weight: 400;
                    line-height: 1.5;">
                    Puzzled by The Sixth Sense, Glass, or Split, and their twisted endings? <i>Trap</i> is another psychological thriller by director M. Night Shyamalan. At first glance, it seems like a dad movie, but the plot centers on the psychopathic urges of a killer and the genuine affection for a daughter.</p>
                    <p style="color: #E7EDF0;
                    font-size: 17px;
                    font-style: normal;
                    font-weight: 400;
                    line-height: 1.5;">
                    Josh Hartnett in the father role and as notorious serial killer The Butcher executes a frame worth honoring. All intended intense scenes are well locked, and the indirect adaptation of the real-life sting operation, Operation Flagship, is well recreated. </p>
                    <p style="color: #E7EDF0;
                    font-size: 17px;
                    font-style: normal;
                    font-weight: 400;
                    line-height: 1.5;">
                    <i>Trap</i> is simply that type of mystery thriller that grips the viewer's attention and makes you wonder what’s coming next. </p>
