                    font-style: normal;
                    font-weight: 400;
                    line-height: 1.5;">
                    <i>The Last of Us</i> takes a hard blow on humans’ darkest fears, on the survival of the human species. The show, in a candid review, is an escape from the curse of video game adaptations. </p>
                    <p style="color: #E7EDF0;
                    font-size: 17px;
                    font-style: normal;
                    font-weight: 400;
                    line-height: 1.5;">What takes this adaptation a notch higher is the constant focus on moral and psychological pressure, typically on who to kill. Though some episodes deviate from the original plot and survival theme, the series effectively immerses us in the storylines of Pascal’s Joel and Bella Ramsey’s Ellie.</p>
                    <p style="color: #E7EDF0;
                    font-size: 17px;
                    font-style: normal;
                    font-weight: 400;
                    line-height: 1.5;">The plot of <i>The Last of Us</i> is what drives the massive success of season 1, which revolves around a parasitic fungal infection that ravaged the planet in 2003. In the aftermath, humans are turned into violent creatures known as the “Infected”.</p>
                    <p style="color: #E7EDF0;
                    font-size: 17px;
